Highlander Jeep with registration number RBC 398 JM was among the items recovered. Idris said he will be charged to court as soon as investigation is completed. Vanguard News Nigeria The Nigeria Security and Civil Defence Corps (NSCDC) in Nasarawa State has arrested a 21-year-old suspected candidate for being in possession of firearms in one of the centres of the ongoing Unified Tertiary Matriculation Examination (UTME) in the state. May 18, 2017 In "News" The Nigeria Security and Civil Defence Corps (NSCDC) says it has arrested a 25-year-old tricycle rider for allegedly attempting to defile a 15-year-old girl at Brigate area, Nasarawa Local Government Area, Kano State. NSCDC Commandant in Kano State, Mr. Abu Abdu, disclosed this to newsmen while parading the suspect on… June 27, 2020 In "News" The Nigerian Security and Civil Defence Corps (NSCDC)in Cross River on Sunday said that it arrested 15 suspected oil thieves between January and March. April 3, 2016 In "News"